                            <comment id="17132718" author="kkrugler" created="Wed, 10 Jun 2020 21:06:00 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Who generated this badly broken HTML file? I ran it through my checker, and got 4,623 errors and 262 warnings (possibly a record for any file I&apos;ve looked at).&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17132719" author="kkrugler" created="Wed, 10 Jun 2020 21:08:01 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Also I tried opening it with Google Chrome, and it choked. I was able to open it with Safari.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17132723" author="younes" created="Wed, 10 Jun 2020 21:17:37 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=kkrugler&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;kkrugler&quot;&gt;kkrugler&lt;/a&gt; this HTML main purpose was to pinpoint the &lt;b&gt;iframe&lt;/b&gt; indexing issue.&lt;br/&gt;
 How about this simple &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/elastic/elasticsearch/issues/57924#issuecomment-642016522&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;one&lt;/a&gt; from &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=dadoonet&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;dadoonet&quot;&gt;dadoonet&lt;/a&gt;:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
&amp;lt;html&amp;gt;
&amp;lt;body&amp;gt;
outside
&amp;lt;iframe srcdoc=&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;&amp;lt;html&amp;gt;&amp;lt;body&amp;gt;content iframe&amp;lt;/body&amp;gt;&amp;lt;/html&amp;gt;&quot;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;gt;&amp;lt;/iframe&amp;gt;
&amp;lt;/body&amp;gt;
&amp;lt;/html&amp;gt;
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17132724" author="kkrugler" created="Wed, 10 Jun 2020 21:17:49 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Over at [Elasticsearch|&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/elastic/elasticsearch/issues/57924&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/elastic/elasticsearch/issues/57924&lt;/a&gt;], there&apos;s a shorter HTML file that supposedly doesn&apos;t work:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
&amp;lt;html&amp;gt;
&amp;lt;body&amp;gt;
outside
&amp;lt;iframe srcdoc=&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;&amp;lt;html&amp;gt;&amp;lt;body&amp;gt;content iframe&amp;lt;/body&amp;gt;&amp;lt;/html&amp;gt;&quot;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;gt;&amp;lt;/iframe&amp;gt;
&amp;lt;/body&amp;gt;
&amp;lt;/html&amp;gt; &lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17132729" author="kkrugler" created="Wed, 10 Jun 2020 21:29:33 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I&apos;m guessing the issue is that the &lt;tt&gt;srcdoc&lt;/tt&gt; attribute isn&apos;t given special handling inside of an &lt;tt&gt;iframe&lt;/tt&gt; element. In theory browser support for &lt;tt&gt;srcdoc&lt;/tt&gt;&#160;is optional, and the browser can fall back to the URL in the &lt;tt&gt;src&lt;/tt&gt; attribute. I think this attribute was added in HTLM5. Supporting this is &quot;interesting&quot;, in that it&apos;s actually an embedded document, and thus should be processed in the same manner as other (non-HTML) formats that support embedded documents. E.g. metadata from the embedded HTML should be exposed, etc.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;(I&apos;m not sure I&apos;d classify this as a major bug...)&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17132734" author="tallison@mitre.org" created="Wed, 10 Jun 2020 21:33:29 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Please tell me you can&apos;t embed a pdf file in there....&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;But seriously, we could add processing for this as an embedded document or &quot;parse it inline&quot;?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17132737" author="kkrugler" created="Wed, 10 Jun 2020 21:38:53 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I think we have to treat it as an embedded document, because we&apos;ll want a full HTML parse (with all of the complicated logic to try to handle edge cases) since that&apos;s basically what it is (full HTML doc, starting with optional &lt;tt&gt;DOCTYPE&lt;/tt&gt; and then the &lt;tt&gt;&amp;lt;html&amp;gt;&lt;/tt&gt; element). See&#160;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.w3.org/TR/2010/WD-html5-20101019/author/the-iframe-element.html#attr-iframe-srcdoc&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://www.w3.org/TR/2010/WD-html5-20101019/author/the-iframe-element.html#attr-iframe-srcdoc&lt;/a&gt;&#160;for more details.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17132740" author="tallison@mitre.org" created="Wed, 10 Jun 2020 21:45:13 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Head hurts...I guess we have to handle &lt;tt&gt;src=&quot;data:&lt;/tt&gt; as well in the same way?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://stackoverflow.com/questions/19739001/which-is-the-difference-between-srcdoc-and-src-datatext-html-in-an&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://stackoverflow.com/questions/19739001/which-is-the-difference-between-srcdoc-and-src-datatext-html-in-an&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17132744" author="tallison@mitre.org" created="Wed, 10 Jun 2020 21:50:51 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Wait, we already are...&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/tika/blob/master/tika-parsers/src/main/java/org/apache/tika/parser/html/HtmlHandler.java#L181&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/tika/blob/master/tika-parsers/src/main/java/org/apache/tika/parser/html/HtmlHandler.java#L181&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This should be fairly straightforward.  I can probably take this next week unless someone wants to beat me to it.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
